<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910726-0052</DOCNO><DOCID>910726-0052.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- InterVoice Inc.:   Group of Bermuda Investors   Reports Buying 5.2% Stake</HL><DATE>07/26/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   INTV</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>BERMUDA (BD)NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   A group comprising Orbis Investment Management Ltd. andPosAlpha Management Ltd., both Bermuda investment managers,said it holds a 5.2% stake in InterVoice Inc.'s common sharesoutstanding.   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,the group said it holds 220,000 shares that it purchased fromJune 4 to July 10 for $11 to $12.25 each.</LP><TEXT>   According to the filing, the group purchased the shares tomake a long-term investment in InterVoice.   InterVoice, based in Dallas, makes telephonecall-automation equipment.</TEXT></DOC>